Investor FAQs - Capital Bank Financial



















































Investor Relations








Investor FAQs
 
Show all 

 On what stock exchange are Capital Bank shares traded, and what is the ticker symbol? 

	The Capital Bank ticker is CBF and it is traded on the NASDAQ Global Select Market.

 When was Capital Bank's Initial Public Offering? 

	September 20, 2012.

 Where is Capital Bank's corporate headquarters? 

	333 Fayetteville Street
	Raleigh, NC 27601

 Who are the members of Capital Bank's Board of Directors? 

	You can view our Board of Directors by visiting the Board of Directors section of our Investor Relations website.

 Who are the members of the Capital Bank's management team? 

	You can view our management team by visiting the Management section of our Investor Relations website.

 When does Capital Bank's fiscal year end? 

	31 December

 Does Capital Bank pay dividends? 

	The Company expects to pay a regular quarterly dividend, subject to approval by the Company's board of directors. Please see the latest quarterly earnings press release for details.

 Does Capital Bank have a direct stock purchase plan? 

	Capital Bank does not currently have a direct stock purchase plan.

 Where can I find all of Capital Bank's SEC filings? Where can I download and view quarterly and annual reports? 

	Quarterly and annual reports, as well as other SEC filings, can be accessed on the Financial Information portion of our Investor Relations website or directly from the SEC at www.sec.gov.

 How do I contact Investor Relations with a question or request? 

	You can contact Capital Bank Investor Relations by telephone at 704.554.5901, or fill out the form below.

 Do you have another question that hasn't been answered?

Please submit your question using the form below.






