Capital Bank Financial Corp. Key Developments

Capital Bank Financial Reports Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the Second Quarter Ended June 30, 2017
Jul 20 17
Capital Bank Financial reported unaudited consolidated earnings results for the second quarter ended June 30, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported net income of $23,806,000 or $0.45 per diluted share compared to net income of $17,441,000 or $0.40 per diluted share reported in the same period last year. Interest and dividend income was $97,286,000 against $69,579,000 reported last year. Net interest income was $85,242,000 against $61,515,000 reported last year. Income before income taxes was $37,954,000 against $27,729,000 reported last year. Return on average assets was 0.95% against 0.93% reported last year. Return on average shareholders equity was 7.20% against 6.88% reported last year. Core net income was $26,703,000 or $0.50 per share against $26,703,000 or $0.45 per share reported last year. Tangible book value per share at the end of the period was $20.76 against $20.22 reported last year.


Capital Bank Financial Corp. Declares Dividend, Payable on August 21, 2017
Jul 20 17
Capital Bank Financial Corp. declared a cash dividend of $0.12 per share, payable on August 21, 2017, to shareholders of record as of August 7, 2017.


Capital Bank Financial Corp. Amends By-Laws
May 5 17
On May 3, 2017, the Board of Directors of Capital Bank Financial Corp., having determined that it was in the best interests of Capital Bank and its stockholders to amend the by-laws of Capital Bank (the By-Laws), by resolution authorized, approved and adopted an amendment to the By-Laws that became effective on May 3, 2017 (the By-Law Amendment).


